Falling Steel Plates Kill Four , Injure 52
XINING , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Falling steel plates killed four people and injured 52 at a construction site in northwest China 's Qinghai Province on Saturday .
On September 19 at 11 : 25 in the morning , the steel mold plates , used for pouring concrete , fell from a height of 20 meters during the construction of a cooling tower at the Qiaotou Power Plant .
Dozens of workers fell to the ground , four died and 52 others were seriously injured .
Local government and construction company leaders rushed to the scene immediately after the accident occurred .
All the injured were taken to the hospitals .
The cause of the accident is under investigation .
